---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Read the Privacy Policy for Student Utility Hub to understand how we protect and process your academic records and cookies."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <span class="rounded-full border border-hairline bg-canvas px-3 py-1 font-mono text-xs font-semibold text-mute">
      Legal
    </span>
    <h1 class="mt-4 font-sans text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.96px] text-ink sm:text-4xl">
      Privacy Policy.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-mute font-mono">
      Last updated: June 9, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body">
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">
          1. Information We Collect
        </h2>
        <p>
          At <strong>Student Utility Hub</strong>, we prioritize user privacy. Unlike traditional academic trackers, we **do not collect or store your personal academic data** (such as attendance percentages, credit scores, or individual grades) on our servers.
        </p>
        <p>
          All data entry occurs client-side and is stored exclusively within your browser's **LocalStorage** for your personal convenience. You may delete this data at any time by clearing your browser cache.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">
          2. Cookies and Log Files
        </h2>
        <p>
          We use standard browser logging to track server errors and analyze traffic trends. We collect basic information including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside flex flex-col gap-2 pl-2">
          <li>Internet Protocol (IP) addresses</li>
          <li>Browser type and version</li>
          <li>Referring/exit pages and timestamps</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is anonymized and used solely to diagnose hosting performance on Cloudflare Pages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">
          3. Advertising Partners & Google AdSense
        </h2>
        <p>
          We may partner with third-party advertising networks, such as Google AdSense, to display ads on the website. These partners may use cookies, web beacons, or tracking technologies to serve advertisements based on your visits to our site and other sites on the internet.
        </p>
        <p>
          Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to our users based on their visit to our site and/or other sites on the Internet. Users may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting Google's Ad Settings page.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">
          4. Contact Information
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us via our <a href="/contact" class="text-link hover:underline">Contact Form</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
